%T A207075 629584,1029781,1944261,3670641,6003160,11333140,21395220,34990137,
%U A207075 66055537,124701637,203938620,385001040,726815560,1188642541,2243951661,4236192681,6927917584
%N A207075 Nonnegative values x of solutions (x, y) to the Diophantine equation x^2 + (x+479)^2 = y^2.
%C A207075 For the generic case x^2 + (x + p)^2 = y^2 with p = m^2 - 50 a (prime) number, m >= 19 (p >= 311), the first three consecutive solutions are (0, p), (10*m+50, m^2+10*m+50), (3*m^2-50*m+200, 5*m^2-70*m+250), the subsequent solutions are defined by the following recurrence relation:(X(n), Y(n)) = (3*X(n-3) + 2*Y(n-3) + p, 4*X(n-3) + 3*Y(n-3) + 2*p), X(n) = 6*X(n-3) - X(n-6) + 2*p, and Y(n) = 6*Y(n-3) - Y(n-6) (can be easily proved using X(n) = 3*X(n-3) + 2*Y(n-3) + p, and Y(n) = 4*X(n-3) + 3*Y(n-3) + 2*p). - _Mohamed Bouhamida_, Jun 18 2026
%H A207075 Vincenzo Librandi, <a href="/A207075/b207075.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%H A207075 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/DiophantineEquation.html">Diophantine Equation</a>.
%H A207075 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diophantine_equation">Diophantine equation</a>.
%H A207075 <a href="/index/Rec#order_07">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (1,0,6,-6,0,-1,1).
%F A207075 G.f.: x^2*(180*x^5 + 119*x^4 + 180*x^3 - 800*x^2 - 357*x - 280)/((x-1)*(x^6-6*x^3+1)). - _Colin Barker_, Aug 05 2012
%e A207075 For p=479 (m=23) the first three consecutive solutions are (0, 479), (280, 809), (637, 1285).
%t A207075 LinearRecurrence[{1, 0, 6, -6, 0, -1, 1}, {0, 280, 637, 1437, 2937, 4960, 9580}, 50]
%Y A207075 Cf. A205672, A207058, A207059, A207060, A207061.
